-- Hughes or Zola May be Appointed as QPR Coach, the Sun Says: Soccer Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2012-01-09T09:41:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-09/hughes-or-zola-may-be-appointed-as-qpr-coach-the-sun-says-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  QPR Coach  Former Fulham coach Mark Hughes and ex-West Ham manager
Gianfranco Zola are candidates to take charge at Queens Park
Rangers,  the Sun  reported.  Hughes quit Fulham in the last offseason and missed out on
becoming Aston Villa manager when  Alex McLeish  got the job,
according to the Sun. QPR fired  Neil Warnock  yesterday.  Newcastle Clause  The release clause of Newcastle’s Demba Ba is about half
the 10 million pounds ($12.1 million) mooted over the weekend,
the  Daily Mirror  reported, citing Tottenham coach  Harry Redknapp .  Several teams will investigate whether to poach the
striker, who has scored 15 times this season, the Mirror said.  Arsenal Enquiry  Arsenal asked about buying Chelsea’s Salomon Kalou for 3
million pounds, the  Daily Mail  reported.  The Gunners made an official approach after the Blues
stalled on the Ivory Coast striker’s 90,000 pounds-a-week wage
request, according to the Mail.  Blackburn Target  Blackburn is planning to sign 20-year-old Bastia winger
Wahbi Khazri for about 1 million pounds, the  Daily Mirror 
reported.  Coach  Steve Kean  needs a replacement for Junior Hoilett,
who could join Bolton when his contract expires after this
season, the Mirror said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
